IN marking its 20 years of services in the country, DCB Bank is set to enter into strategic partnership with key stakeholders in order to enhance financial services in the country reach the underserved communities. This was said in Dar es Salaam on Tuesday by the DCB Managing Director Mr Godfrey Ndalahwa at the launch of the 20 years commemoration of the DCB services in the country. “The strategic partnership with key stakeholders is part of the commemoration of the 20 years of DCB Bank’s services in the country and way to enhance further its services reach the intended communities,” he said. To realise this initiative, Mr Ndalahwa said the bank will enter into a strategic partnership with development partners, governments, the private sector and local and international organization. He added that the 20 years of the banking services in the country is a clear testimony on how DCB is committed to impact on the lives of Tanzanians by working alongside a range of well-placed partners in creating and sharing value for the communities. He said the bank is well positioned to continue providing innovative banking services and financial products that would contribute more to social and economic development while generating profit for shareholders. DCB bank has nine branches, more than 1,000 DCB Wakala Agents and 280 Umoja switch ATM’s serving over three million customers across the country.